                  <interp inst="t18310908-227-crimeloc1165" type="placeName" value="Bedfont"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-227-crimeloc1165" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-227-off1163 t18310908-227-crimeloc1165"></join>. On Sunday evening, the 21st of August, I heard my two geese making a noise; I sent my daughter to fetch them in, and we missed a brown goose.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. You had only two? A. No; I had seen the prisoner that day - I believe he was forward in liquor.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-227-person1695">
                  CHARLOTTE 
                  TILLYER
               <interp inst="t18310908-227-person1695" type="surname" value="TILLYER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-227-person1695" type="given" value="CHARLOTTE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-227-person1695" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the daughter of the last<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183109080106"></xptr>witness. When we missed one of the geese I followed the prisoner, and overtook him with it in his hand; I asked him to give it to me - he refused, he pushed me out of the pathway and threw the goose into a ditch; it was not quite dead then - the prisoner had a dog; he called the dog, and set it at me - it did not bite me; I got the goose, and took it home - I think he was in liquor; he was not above one hundred yards from our house then.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Did you not see the dog attack the goose? A. No; the dog was before him, but he had the goose in his hand.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence What she says is all false; I never saw the goose till it was brought into a public-house where I was taken.</p>
               <p>The prisoner received a good character.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18310908-227-verdict1166" type="verdictDescription">
